    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1565"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/96.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Ambassador</gloss> to Counselor
                            <persName type="to">Lansing</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 17, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Counselor</hi>: I have received from the Boleo
                    Company a telegram stating that serious troubles have apparently begun once more
                    at Santa Rosalia, the Mexican garrison having, it is reported, revolted and the
                    life of the employees of the company being threatened.</p>
                <p>If it were possible for the American Government to ascertain how the matter
                    stands and to supply such protection as may be needed, I should be very much
                    obliged. The same has been done before and my Government has highly appreciated
                    the usefulness of your intervention. I hope it will be possible to act again as
                    was previously done.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
